# Python worker standards — {{WORKSPACE_NAME}}

> **Purpose**: The authoritative engineering-conventions document for event-driven Python workers in this workspace — Lambda handlers, SQS / SNS / Kinesis consumers, Celery tasks, Kafka consumers, scheduled jobs, batch ETL. **How we write workers here**, not architecture (that's `platform.md`).
> **Last Updated**: {{DATE}}
> **Bootstrapped by**: PipeCrew `/discover` — Phase B2.5.

Workers differ from API services: there's no HTTP contract, the input is an event schema (JSON Schema / Avro / Protobuf), and the success criterion is "handled-or-DLQ'd, never lost". This document captures the workspace's conventions for those concerns.

**Stable section anchors (§1–§9) are cited by number from implementer and reviewer agents.** Do not renumber existing sections; you may add §10+.

